story.storyDescription: Sarah finds a dead body in the woods and uncovers a dark and deadly mystery.
story.title: Littlefield - Part 13

messages.text: Corinne, are you there??
Who is this??
It’s Wayne again!
My folks and I loaded into the van and stopped at The Barn...
...to see if we could find your sister. Nobody was inside.
I told them to drive to your house to see if we could help you guys get out of there.
Are you inside?
I’m not in my house right now...
and haven’t been since I tried to look for my sister by myself.
I’m sorry about that. You have to understand...
I was worried about my family
Wayne, it’s Sarah
What!!? She found you??? ARE YOU OKAY??
I’m fine.
Who were those men?? Were they the fucking government like I thought??
Yes. I can’t rehash that right now.
We’re speeding down Highway 37 in New Hampshire
What!? How did you cross the state lines??
We tried to leave a three hours ago, but they only let those buses in
How did you know about the buses two hours ago
My Dad found out from a friend
I’m assuming you heard about St. Rhiannon on twitter
Everybody on twitter has.
Yeah, well it’s blowing up because of us.
What?
These asshole guards refused to let us through, so Jared tweeted about it
That guy from the party??
The guy who saved my ass
People started showing up in droves, and once they did...
they made it a bit easier for us to get through.
So you outnumbered the guards by everyone breaking through?
Yes, a couple of guards got run over. Smoke bomb was thrown.
But since they wouldn’t let us through....
We have another place for you to go.
My Dad doesn’t think they’re going to let anyone in at this St. Rhiannon.
They have no fucking choice now. We’re one of so many cars headed that way.
He said a friend of his in New Hampshire said it’s set up like Fort Knox
And even if they do let people in...
they are going to be overrun by everyone in the tri-state area who knows about it.
Not to mention all the noise is going to draw all of THEM to you
So be it. Everyone gets the same freedom or nobody.
Well that’s stupid. You might as well be safe.
We have this farm, it’s really secluded
Yeah, well we can’t go with you because our parents are at St. Rhiannon right now.
How are they there without you??
It involves a lot of lying on the cops’ part.
They think we’re coming there
We have a big van, we can probably fit all of you, if they leave.
We’re not going to leave to go to some farm with you when we can live on some compound.
Like I said, the farm is safer.
Not to mention we’ve already discussed my father’s large gun collection.
We have a bunch on the car with us now, and we have even more at the farm.
That’s disturbing.
Well, my Dad has always been a doomsday prepper...
which is something I kept secret because I thought it was embarrassing...
but here we are...
Why do you care so much about me and my family being safe??
Listen, I just moved here, and you are one of the first friends I have.
This place is going to be run into the ground Sarah, just get everyone to come with us
Sarah??
Fine...suit yourself
Wait! It’s Corinne again! We need help
What happened??
Some car full of people with guns just drove through and started shooting everyone’s tires!
We just spun out and hit the median.
Is everyone okay??
Sarah hit her head against the glass and is bleeding, but conscious.
And Jared’s Mom got knocked out. The tires are done.
We have to get to our parents!! Please help!!
We were going in the opposite direction. Where are you?
We’re on Highway 37 right before the Kingstown exit.
My Dad said we’ll go.
The problem is the whole highway is plugging up because we weren’t the only ones hit.
What if they come back with their guns?
They won’t. They want to beat you to where you’re going.
Like I told your sister, we’re heavily stocked and ready to go.
Oh my God, they’re circling back around.
Okay, it looks like if you go right off the exit, there is a Soire Diner.
It’s not that far at all. Do you guys think you can run there?
Yes.
We’re on our way.
